                    <div class="col-md-8">
                        <p>The goal of this experiment is to evaluate the effectiveness of tactile internet technology, using a tactile glove and the Meta Quest 3, in transmitting tactile sensations of textures available on a website. Users will experience these sensations and fill out a form to indicate their perceptions.</p>
                        <p>The tactile sensations are developed using vibration feedback through PWM signals, altering the duty cycle and frequency parameters. The perception of these sensations may vary depending on the system latency. The data resulting from the form completion will be used to train a machine learning (ML) model that will receive the type of texture and indicate the appropriate parameters to represent this texture as a tactile sensation through vibration feedback. The ML model learns from a database and adjusts for the correct vibration; depending on the latency, the vibration parameters may change.</p>
                        <p>Additionally, latency can be used to generate a Quality of Experience (QoE) equation to be used in analyses. Filters can be applied to compensate for the delay, ensuring a better tactile experience for users.</p>
